Olive Oil
1 knob ginger
10 g butter
1.5 cup water
¼ tsp salt (for the rice)
1 packet basmati rice
2 clove garlic
1 carrot
1 bag green beans
1 packet Asian Greens
1 packet garlic aioli
1 packet Japanese Dressing
1 packet pork schnitzels
2.5 tbs plain flour
½ tsp salt (for the pork)
1 egg
1 packet panko breadcrumbs
1 sachet black sesame seeds
1 tbs soy sauce
2 bunch spring onion
½ Fresh Chilli

Finely grate the ginger. In a medium saucepan, melt the butter and a dash of olive oil over a medium heat. Cook the ginger until fragrant, 1-2 minutes. Add the water and salt (for the rice) and bring to the boil. Add the basmati rice, stir, cover with a lid and reduce the heat to low. Cook for 10 minutes, then remove the pan from the heat and keep covered until the rice is tender and the water is absorbed, 10-15 minutes.
TIP: The rice will finish cooking in its own steam so don't peek!

While the rice is cooking, finely chop the garlic. Thinly slice the carrot into half-moons. Trim the green beans and cut into 2cm pieces. Roughly chop the Asian greens. In a small bowl, combine the garlic aioli and Japanese dressing. Set aside.

Pull apart the pork schnitzels (they may be stuck together). In a shallow bowl, combine the plain flour and salt (for the pork), then season with pepper. In a second shallow bowl, whisk the egg. In a third shallow bowl, combine the panko breadcrumbs and black sesame seeds. Dip the pork schnitzels into the flour mixture, followed by the egg, and finally into the panko-sesame mixture. Transfer to a plate.

In a large frying pan, heat a drizzle of olive oil over a medium-high heat. Cook the carrot and green beans, until tender, 5-6 minutes. Add the Asian greens and cook until just wilted, 1 minute. Add the garlic and soy sauce and cook, stirring, until fragrant, 1 minute. Transfer to a bowl.

Return the frying pan to a medium-high heat with enough olive oil to coat the base of the pan. Cook the crumbed pork, in batches, until golden and cooked through, 2-3 minutes each side. Transfer to a plate lined with paper towel.

Thinly slice the spring onion. Thinly slice the long green chilli (if using). Slice the sesame crumbed pork. Divide the ginger rice between bowls. Top with the garlicky veggies and pork. Garnish with the spring onion and chilli. Serve with the Japanese mayo.